\sum_{k=1}^{\infty} \frac{(-1)^{k+1}}{k} = \log{2}
\sum_{k=1}^{\infty} (-1)^{k+1} \left ( \frac{1}{k} + \frac{1}{k+1} \right ) = \log{2} + (1-\log{2}) = 1
